#3001
@@WCedar Square@@N~
The avenue broadens here into a lived-in civic pocket where couriers and fishmongers repeatedly cross paths under strings of practical @@ylanterns@@N. The air carries wet stone and ash, while distant hymnwork rises and falls between facades of stone and timber that have been repaired many times over generations. Underfoot, the paving shifts through inlaid ward sigils, and at the edge of the street stands a public fountain carved with lions, giving this stretch of @@WMidgaard@@N a character all its own.~
