The avenue broadens here into a lived-in civic pocket where apothecaries and couriers repeatedly cross paths under strings of practical @@ylanterns@@N. The air carries hot iron scale, while measured drill calls rises and falls between facades of stone and timber that have been repaired many times over generations. Underfoot, the paving shifts through painted survey marks, and at the edge of the street stands a prayer rail polished to a shine, giving this stretch of @@WMidgaard@@N a character all its own.~
